<recipe>
<title>
Easy Peach Cobbler
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 20 minutes
COOK TIME: 25 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 45 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: cobbler, dessert, peach
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
FILLING
4 cups frozen peaches thawed
1/2 cup brown sugar
1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
1/4 teaspoon almond extract
1 tablespoon all-purpose flour
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Generously grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Place the sliced peaches in a bowl; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon, almond extract, and flour. Mix gently.
Spread evenly in dish.
Combine all dry ingredients for cobbler crust in a bowl.
Cut in the butter with a pastry cutter or your fingers, to make the texture like coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk; stir to form a soft dough.
Drop rounded spoonfuls of dough on top.
Sprinkle with the tablespoon of raw sugar.
Bake until fruit is bubbly and crust topping is golden brown, about 20-25 minutes.
</instructions>
</recipe>
